{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":52811,"name":"Graham Morrison","username":"degville","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.snapcraft.io/degville/{size}/2021_2.png","created_at":"2019-07-31T15:23:33.597Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThe \u003ca href=\"https://snapcraft.io/store\"\u003eSnap Store\u003c/a\u003e web UI can be used to track installation and usage statistics for snaps published with your developer account.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo accomplish this, the store assigns an anonymous identifier, the device-serial, to every new \u003cem\u003esnapd\u003c/em\u003e client it sees. This exchange usually happens when a new installation contacts the store, and the identifier persists for the lifespan of the machine.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSystems running snapd will periodically make a refresh request to the store, checking the for the most recent release of each installed snap. At that moment, they inform the store of their device-serial along with a list of the currently installed snaps. The store simply infers the list of active applications from the clients’ requests in a given period.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo access the Snap Store, simply go to \u003ca href=\"https://snapcraft.io/store\"\u003ehttps://snapcraft.io/store\u003c/a\u003e and login with your developer account credentials. See \u003ca href=\"/t/using-the-snap-store/12379\"\u003eUsing the Snap Store\u003c/a\u003e if you don’t yet have an account, and have yet to publish snaps to the store.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSnap Store metrics can also be retrieved with \u003ca href=\"/t/snapcraft-metrics/25732\"\u003e\u003ccode\u003esnapcraft metrics\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/a\u003e command.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eMy published snaps\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo see a list of snaps published with the currently logged in developer account, select \u003cem\u003eMy published snaps\u003c/em\u003e from the account drop-down menu in the top right of the web UI.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis page contains a table listing each published snap, with columns to indicate whether a snap is public, its release channel and a corresponding release version.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA chart at the top tracks install numbers for each snap, and rolling over a position in this chart will show individual numbers for a specific time point.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://assets.ubuntu.com/v1/d5f5baf9-snap-installs.png\" title=\"Screenshot_20190731_112921\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://assets.ubuntu.com/v1/d5f5baf9-snap-installs.png\" alt=\"Screenshot_20190731_112921\" width=\"679\" height=\"500\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eScreenshot_20190731_112921\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e874×643\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eSnap metrics\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo see individual metrics for a snap, click the snap from the published snaps page and select the \u003cem\u003eMetrics\u003c/em\u003e tab. This page is split into two, with the top-half showing active devices and the lower half showing installation territories.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe default active device interval 30 days, and this counts each unique device refresh request for the given snap, reported as installed at least once during a rolling day day period. A drop-down menu changes this interval to a period between, and including, 7 days to 2 years.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://assets.ubuntu.com/v1/f18471f3-snap-metrics.png\" title=\"Install metrics\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://assets.ubuntu.com/v1/f18471f3-snap-metrics.png\" alt=\"Install metrics\" width=\"690\" height=\"345\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eInstall metrics\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e2000×1000\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe default breakdown of active devices is by \u003cem\u003eversion\u003c/em\u003e, illustrated by the colour of the filled sections of the chart. These sections help to visualise when and how many users are automatically updated from one version to another after a release. Hover the cursor over any section to see the colour-\u0026gt;version key.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAs with the count interval, the breakdown can be switched from \u003cem\u003eBy version\u003c/em\u003e  to either \u003cem\u003eBy OS\u003c/em\u003e or \u003cem\u003eBy channel\u003c/em\u003e from its drop-down menu:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eBy OS\u003c/strong\u003e: view the number of active users on each Linux distribution over your selected time-frame. This can help you target integration issues that may be specific to popular distributions.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eBy channel\u003c/strong\u003e: view how many installations are tracking each \u003ca href=\"/t/channels/551\"\u003echannel\u003c/a\u003e of your snap. Depending on how a snap uses channels, this can be useful to ascertain stability vs. cutting edge features for a snap’s user base.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://assets.ubuntu.com/v1/e2a6f31e-snap-weekly-devices.png\" alt=\"Screenshot_20190731_155049\" width=\"690\" height=\"374\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eTerritories\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe final visualisation on the Snap Store \u003cem\u003eMetrics\u003c/em\u003e page shows the geographical region where a snap is installed. Studying the demography of a snap can help when allocating resources for potential localisation efforts and geographic adoption.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRoll over a region to reveal the specific number of users for that territory.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://assets.ubuntu.com/v1/0decea5d-snap-territories.png\" alt=\"Screenshot_20190731_160226\" width=\"690\" height=\"411\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-11-24T12:49:32.722Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":176,"reads":32,"readers_count":31,"score":866.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":12556,"topic_slug":"snap-store-metrics","display_username":"Graham Morrison","primary_group_name":null,"primary_group_flair_url":null,"primary_group_flair_bg_color":null,"primary_group_flair_color":null,"version":5,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://snapcraft.io/store","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Install Linux apps using the Snap Store | Snapcraft","clicks":1},{"url":"https://assets.ubuntu.com/v1/d5f5baf9-snap-installs.png","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"d5f5baf9-snap-installs.png","clicks":0},{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/using-the-snap-store/12379","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Using the Snap Store","clicks":0},{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/channels/551","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Channels","clicks":0},{"url":"https://assets.ubuntu.com/v1/f18471f3-snap-metrics.png","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"f18471f3-snap-metrics.png","c